Introduction

Sumin is a South Korean singer-songwriter, rapper, and dancer under High Up Entertainment. She is best known as the leader and the oldest member of the girl group STAYC.

On September 9, 2020, Sumin was the second member of STAYC to be announced. She debuted with the group on November 12, 2020 when they released their first single album "Star To A Young Culture".
